## 5. Services Architecture

Each service is a plain Python class. No magic — just dependency injection via FastAPI `Depends()`.

### Service Responsibilities

```
CampaignService
  ├── create_campaign(user_id, params) → Campaign
  ├── get_campaign(campaign_id, user_id) → Campaign
  └── list_campaigns(user_id) → List[Campaign]

ChatService
  ├── process_message(session_id, message, user) → ChatResponse
  ├── save_session(session_id, extracted_params) → CampaignSession
  └── get_session(session_id) → CampaignSession

LLMService  ← CENTRALIZED. Used by ChatService AND ProcessorService
  ├── chat_completion(messages, provider, model, system_prompt) → str
  ├── generate_email(contact, campaign_session, user_profile) → EmailDraft
  └── extract_params(raw_message, campaign_type) → ExtractedParams (JSON)

ProcessorService  ← runs inside background worker
  ├── run_research(campaign_id) → List[Contact]
  ├── dispatch_agents(contacts, campaign_session) → None
  └── generate_all_drafts(contacts, campaign_session) → List[EmailJob]

ApolloService
  └── search_contacts(companies, geography, role_title) → List[Contact]

ScraperService
  └── scrape_contacts(companies, geography) → List[Contact]  # bounce_risk=True

GoogleDriveService
  ├── get_resume_text(user_id) → str
  └── fetch_file(file_id, oauth_token) → bytes

EmailService
  ├── send_via_gmail(email_job_id) → SendResult
  ├── check_daily_limit(user_id) → bool
  └── update_send_stats(email_job_id, event) → None
```

